If we are running mvn package k8s:build for the first time, we cannot retrieve last modified time of previous artifact. We get an IOException. 

Regardless of whether we get this IOException, we must save the last modified time of the current output artifact, so this step goes in the finally block. 
Saving the last modfied time can also result in IOException. 
We cannot treat both these exceptions as same, hence two try catch blocks.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 28, 8, 59, 26, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivangMishra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1307151573, 'comment_body': 'This is for code readability.
